GTL, Indian Oil, National Aluminium: India Equity Preview

-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-03-16T01:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/gtl-indian-oil-national-aluminium-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, lost
271.84, or 1.5 percent, to 18,167.64, its steepest decline since
Feb. 24. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange
dropped 1.5 percent to 5,449.65. The BSE 200 Index retreated 1.5
percent to 2,231.68.    GTL Infrastructure Ltd. (GTLI)  : The company is seeking
as much as $300 million from institutional investors and has
hired Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Standard Chartered Plc and
Jefferies Group Inc. to raise the money, according to two people
with direct knowledge of the matter. The shares were unchanged
at 36.6 rupees.  Indian Oil Corp. (IOCL IN): The nation’s largest refiner
increased the price of jet fuel in Mumbai to 59,031.39 rupees a
kiloliter from 55,500.06 rupees a kiloliter earlier, according
to the company’s website. The shares retreated 2.3 percent to
302.85 rupees.  National Aluminium Co. (NACL IN): The company said it
expects to produce 460,000 metric tons of aluminum in the year
ending March 31, 2012. The company will produce 6.3 million tons
of bauxite and 2.1 million tons of alumina in the period, it
said in an e-mailed statement. The shares declined 9.1 percent
to 108.2 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
